<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4674] BooleanValuesTest fails if Xalan is not available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4674</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If Xalan is not available, BooleanValuesTest fails. See for example this error log from the nightly testing:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://dbtg.foundry.sun.com/derby/test/Daily/jvm1.4/testing/Limited/testSummary-947309.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://dbtg.foundry.sun.com/derby/test/Daily/jvm1.4/testing/Limited/testSummary-947309.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The error above is actually caused by the Xalan version bundled with J2SE 1.4.2 being too old for Derby, not that it&apos;s missing. Here&apos;s what the error looks like on Java SE 6 without xalan.jar in the classpath:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) test_01_datatypeCount(org.apache.derbyTesting.functionTests.tests.lang.BooleanValuesTest)java.sql.SQLException: Failed to locate &apos;Xalan&apos; API or implementation classes.  XML operations are not permitted unless these classes are in your classpath.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
